  <body>{`# Strudel Live Coding Reference

Strudel is a live coding music environment (TidalCycles port to JS).
Code is evaluated in a browser REPL.

Use the strudel_set_and_evaluate MCP tool to send code to a running Strudel instance.
Use strudel_get_code to read what's currently playing before making modifications.
Use strudel_stop to silence everything.

## Block Syntax

Each $: defines an independent pattern block. Blocks are separated by blank lines.

    // Lead
    $: note("c4 e4 g4 b4").s("sawtooth").lpf(800)

    // Bass
    $: note("c2 c2 g1 g1").s("sawtooth").lpf(400).decay(.1).sustain(0)

    // Drums
    $: s("bd sd bd [sd bd]").bank("RolandTR909")

Use setcps(n) to set tempo. 0.5 = 120 BPM in 4/4. 1 = 240 BPM.

## Mini Notation

Patterns are written as strings with special syntax:

  space     sequence steps         "bd sd hh" = 3 events per cycle
  *n        speed up (repeat)      "bd*4" = 4 kicks per cycle
  /n        slow down              "bd/2" = 1 kick every 2 cycles
  !n        replicate              "bd!4" = repeat bd 4 times
  <>        alternate per cycle    "<c4 e4 g4>" = different note each cycle
  []        subdivide/group        "[bd sd] hh" = bd+sd in first half
  ,         stack (simultaneous)   "bd, hh*4" = kick + hi-hats together
  ~         silence/rest           "bd ~ sd ~" = kick rest snare rest
  @n        weight/duration        "bd@3 sd" = bd gets 3x duration
  (k,n)     Euclidean rhythm       "bd(3,8)" = 3 hits in 8 steps
  (k,n,r)   Euclidean + rotation   "bd(5,8,-1)" = rotated
  ?         random skip (50%)      "hh?" = randomly drops
  ?0.3      random skip (30%)      "hh?0.3" = 30% chance to skip
  :n        sample variant         "bd:3" = 4th kick variant

## Sound Sources

### Synth oscillators
"sine", "sawtooth", "triangle", "square", "supersaw"

    $: note("c3 e3 g3").s("sawtooth")
    $: note("c2").s("supersaw").detune(rand)

### Noise
"white", "pink", "brown", "crackle"

### Samples
Access via s("name") or s("name:variant"). Available with .bank():

    $: s("bd sd hh cp").bank("RolandTR909")

## Core Functions

### Sound selection
  s("pattern") / sound("pattern")   select sound/sample
  n("pattern")                       sample index or scale degree
  note("pattern")                    note name or MIDI number
  bank("name")                       drum machine bank

### Pitch / Scale
  .scale("root:mode")     quantize to scale: "c:minor", "g:major", "d:dorian"
  .transpose(semitones)    chromatic transpose
  .scaleTranspose(degrees) transpose within scale
  .add(n)                  add to pattern value (arithmetic)
  .detune(amount)          detune in cents. Use rand for random.
  .octave(n)               set octave

### Amplitude Envelope (ADSR)
  .attack(t) / .att(t)      attack time in seconds
  .decay(t) / .dec(t)       decay time
  .sustain(level) / .sus(l)  sustain level 0-1
  .release(t) / .rel(t)     release time

### Filter (Lowpass)
  .lpf(freq) / .cutoff(freq)   lowpass cutoff frequency (Hz)
  .lpq(q) / .resonance(q)      filter resonance/Q
  .lpenv(depth)                 filter envelope depth (positive = sweep up)
  .lpa(t) / .lpattack(t)       filter envelope attack
  .lpd(t) / .lpdecay(t)        filter envelope decay
  .lps(level) / .lpsustain(l)  filter envelope sustain
  .lpr(t) / .lprelease(t)      filter envelope release
  .ftype("ladder")              filter type: "12db", "24db", "ladder" (Moog-style)

### Filter (Highpass / Bandpass)
  .hpf(freq) / .hp(freq)   highpass cutoff
  .bpf(freq) / .bp(freq)   bandpass center
  .hpq(q), .bpq(q)         resonance for each
  .hpenv(depth)             envelope depth for each

### Effects
  .delay(wet)                    delay wet/dry 0-1
  .delaytime(t) / .delayt(t)    delay time in beats
  .delayfeedback(fb)             feedback 0-1
  .room(wet)                     reverb wet/dry
  .roomsize(size) / .size(size)  reverb size
  .pan(p)                        stereo pan 0-1 (0.5 = center)
  .orbit(n) / .o(n)             effect bus routing (different orbits = independent fx)
  .distort(amount)               distortion
  .shape(amount)                 waveshaper saturation
  .crush(bits)                   bitcrusher
  .vowel("a e i o u")           formant filter

### Gain / Volume
  .gain(level)         volume 0-1+
  .velocity(v)         note velocity

### Timing / Structure
  .fast(n)             speed up by factor
  .slow(n)             slow down by factor
  .early(t)            shift earlier in cycle
  .late(t)             shift later
  .struct("pattern")   impose rhythmic structure
  .mask("pattern")     mask on/off
  .euclid(k, n, r)    Euclidean rhythm
  .fit()               stretch sample to fill event duration

### Pattern Transformations
  .rev()                           reverse
  .jux(fn)                         apply function to right channel
  .off(time, fn)                   offset copy with transformation
  .layer(fn1, fn2, ...)           stack multiple transformations
  .superimpose(fn)                 overlay transformed copy
  .echo(times, time, feedback)     echo repetitions
  .ply(n)                          subdivide events
  .chop(n)                         slice sample into n parts

### Conditional / Probabilistic
  .every(n, fn)          apply every nth cycle
  .sometimes(fn)         apply 50% of the time
  .rarely(fn)            apply ~10% of the time
  .sometimesBy(prob, fn) apply with given probability
  .degradeBy(amount)     randomly remove events
  .when(condition, fn)   conditional application

### Signals (continuous values)
Use as arguments to any control parameter:

  sine     0 to 1 sine wave (1 cycle)
  cosine   0 to 1 cosine
  saw      0 to 1 sawtooth ramp
  tri      0 to 1 triangle
  square   0/1 square wave
  rand     random 0 to 1 each event
  perlin   smooth Perlin noise 0 to 1

Modify with .range(min, max), .slow(n), .fast(n):

    .lpf(sine.range(200, 4000).slow(8))   filter sweep over 8 cycles
    .gain(perlin.range(0.3, 1))            organic volume variation
    .detune(rand)                           random detune each note

## Common Patterns

### Acid bass
    $: n("<0 3 5 7>*8").scale("c:minor")
      .s("sawtooth").lpf(600)
      .lpenv(6).lpa(0.005).lpd(0.15).lps(0).lpq(12)
      .ftype("ladder").decay(.1).sustain(0)

### Trance lead
    $: n("<0 4 0 9 7>*16".add("<7 _ _ 6 5 _ _ 6>*2")).scale("g:minor")
      .s("sawtooth").lpf(600).lpenv(7).lpa(0.005).lpd(0.15).lps(0).lpq(12)
      .ftype("ladder").delay(.4).o(3)

### Supersaw pad
    $: n("<7 _ _ 6 5 _ <5 3> <6 4>>*2").scale("g:minor").transpose(-24)
      .s("supersaw").detune(rand)
      .lpf(600).lpenv(8).lpa(0.005).lpd(0.15).lps(0).lpq(12).ftype("ladder")

### 4-on-the-floor with hi-hats
    $: s("bd*4, ~ sd ~ sd, hh*8").bank("RolandTR909")

### Filter sweep automation
    $: note("c2 c2 g1 g1").s("sawtooth")
      .lpf(sine.range(200, 3000).slow(16))
      .lpq(cosine.range(4, 12).slow(8))

### Fake sidechain compression
    .gain("[.2 1@3]*2")   duck on downbeat

### Layered arpeggio
    $: "<eb4 d4 c4 b3>/2"
      .scale("C:minor")
      .struct("[~ x]*2")
      .layer(
        x => x.scaleTranspose(0).early(0),
        x => x.scaleTranspose(2).early(1/8),
        x => x.scaleTranspose(7).early(1/4),
      ).note().s("sawtooth").cutoff(1200).decay(.16).sustain(.3)

## Important Notes

- Always write COMPLETE code (all blocks). Strudel replaces the entire editor.
- Use $: for each independent pattern block, separated by blank lines.
- .o(n) (orbit) routes to separate effect buses — use different numbers
  for different instruments.
- rand is a signal, not a function — use .detune(rand) not .detune(rand()).
- Mini notation strings are auto-parsed. Double-quoted strings in Strudel
  are mini notation.
`}</body>
